Notational Velocity (software)

Notational Velocity is a cult favorite Open Source note-taking app that was originally designed for OSX. Its key feature is its simplicity and speed, allowing users to sync their text notes across different devices using services like Simplenote or Dropbox.

It's popularity was so great that it lead to it's name becoming an expression (see Notation Velocity (expression)).

​
Mozilla Archive Format

The Mozilla Archive Format (MAFF) is a legacy Web archive file format that was provided by Firefox through an extension, used to store one or more web pages with their associated audio, video, and other related web resources to a single file.

The MHTML format is probably always a better option these days.
